title: digits and letters on phone dial
content:
I should probably konw this one myself.. but its kinda generic. I need the help of the experts. What font is this?

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20130107110432im_/http:/typophile.com/files/font_id_6124.jpg)
author: di_ggler

comments.content: Looks a lot like Univers Condensed.
With that y and t it can't be Univers. Isn't the face a little rounded also?

yeah it turns out its not univers. Any other ideas?

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20130107110432im_/http:/typophile.com/files/FONT_ID__6600.jpg)

Didn't see this thread when I answered in the other one.

It's almost like a stretched-out [Chalet Comprimé Cologne 1960](http://web.archive.org/web/20130107110432/http:/www.houseind.com/index.php?page=showfont&id=11&subpage=viewfonts), except for that pesky 'K' again. Are you sure that the upper-case and lower-case are the same typeface?
